U.K. Stocks Fluctuate as Mining Companies Retreat; Banks Climb in London

-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 
2011-09-23T08:03:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/u-k-stocks-fluctuate-as-mining-companies-retreat-banks-climb-in-london.html
U.K. stocks swung between gains and
losses as a selloff in mining companies was offset by gains in
HSBC Holdings Plc.  The FTSE 100 Index rose 0.1 percent at 5,044.4 at 8:58
a.m. in  London  after swinging betweens gains and losses as least
four times in the first hour of trade. The gauge rallied as much
as 1.3 percent at the open.  Antofagasta Plc, Xstrata Plc and Vedanta Resources Plc
all declined more than 2 percent, while HSBC Holdings, the
biggest weighted stock on the FTSE 100, rose 1.7 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sarah Jones at 
 sjones35@bloomberg.net  